cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.CR

This paper deals with adding uncertainty to conditional logics for default reasoning and belief revision, which are topics that are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of probabilities, which is a key concept in machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper touches on the topic of security (cs.CR) by discussing the connection to Lewis's method of imaging, which has applications in cryptography.
